    <requireLicenseAcceptance>false</requireLicenseAcceptance>
    <iconUrl>https://github.com/gep13/ChocolateyPackages/raw/master/calibre/calibre.ico</iconUrl>
    <releaseNotes>
    - New: Support for connecting MTP (non disk based) devices via USB, such as the Nexus 7 and the Kindle Fire HD (Windows Vista and newer and Linux only)
    - New: Calibre Portable: Create a new installer that does not require manually unzipping the Calibre Portable folder. Instead just run the installer and point it to the location you want to install to.
    - New: Calibre Portable: Add support for multiple libraries created inside the 'Calibre Portable' folder.
    - New: In the main book list when editing a blank published date, use a default value of Jan 2000 so that changing the date it easier
    - New: Template language: Add function approximate_formats() to get list of formats saved in the db for a book as opposed to the formats that actually exist on disk
    - New: Template language: Add a couple of new functions to get the path to individual book formats and the calibre library as a whole
    - New: Drivers for HTC Flyer and Trekstor 4ink
    - Fixed: Conversion: Do not error out when tags have unparseable color attributes.
    - Fixed: AZW3 Output: Do not error out if the input document contains embedded fonts of less than 1040 bytes.
    - Fixed: Catalogs: Fix AZW3 output not properly indexed
    - Fixed: Get Books: Remove Beam Books due to lack of response to issues with the store.
    - Fixed: Windows: Ignore drives A: and B: when scanning for the drives belonging to a device
    - Fixed: Kindle driver: Fix generation of apnx files for newer kindle firmware.
    - Fixed: News download: If the output format is set to azw3, generate periodicals in mobi format as amazon does not support azw3 periodicals
    - New News Source: Various Hungarian recipes by laca
    - New News Source: NSFW Corp by Darko Miletic.
    - New News Source: FC Knudde and Stamgasten by drMerry
    - Improved News Source: Indian Express
    - Improved News Source: Anadtech
    - Improved News Source: London Review of Books (subscrption version)
    - Improved News Source: Livemint
    - Improved News Source: xkcd
    - Improved News Source: Doghouse Diaries
    </releaseNotes>
  </metadata>
</package>
